 and strategies that will enable them to become independent  active learners and to achieve academic success  Location  215 Carroll Hall Phone   540  464 7769  Web Site http www vmi edu Miller Academic Center Home  The COL Mike E   DOC  Monsour Center for Cadet Counseling   Center for Cadet Counseling aims to enhance each cadet s ability to benefit academically and personally from the VMI experience  It provides short term counseling the focuses on addressing personal concerns that may impede current and future learning and personal development  Some areas include feelings of depression  loneliness  anxiety  stress  and substance abuse  Location  408 Lejeune Hall Phone   540  464 7667 Web Site  http www vmi edu Content aspx id 10737421908 Chaplain s Office   The Institute Chaplain is the liaison officer to the local churches and is the point of contact for cadets  concerns of a religious or spiritual nature  The Chaplain along with the Commandant s staff provide assistance to cadets in need of an emergency furlough  Location  Old Hospital Phone   540  464 7390 Web Site  http www vmi edu military aspx id 362 cid 15767   Office of Career Services   The Office of Career Services provides a wide array of career planning and employment services  as well as graduate and professional school advising  Location  311 Carroll Hall Phone   540  464 7560 Web Site   http www vmi edu content aspx tid 30043 id 158 Office of Financial Aid   The purpose of the VMI financial aid program is to provide monetary assistance to cadets who  without such aid  would be unable to attend  and to provide aid to cadets with superior abilities  Awards are based on the cadet s demonstrated financial need as determined through the Free Application for Federal Student Aid  FASFA  Forms are available through local high schools and VMI Financial Aid Office  Location  306 Carroll Hall Phone   540  464 7208 Web Site  http www vmi edu Content aspx id 222 Registrar s Office   The Registrar s Office is responsible for functions that include registration  transcript processing  academic standards review  cadet services and academic records management  course scheduling  degree certification and diploma processing  grading and evaluations  statistical reporting and support of ad hoc requests  and FERPA compliance  Location  303 Carroll Hall Phone   540  464 7213 Web Site   http www vmi edu Content aspx id 196 The Institute Honors Program   The Institute Honors Program exists to enrich the academic experience of VMI s outstanding cadets through activities that encourage an affinity for intellectual inquiry and develop the capacity for sophisticated engagement of issues and problems  Web Site   http www vmi edu content aspx id 122 Office of International Programs   The VMI Office of International Programs is tasked with the establishment  promotion  and administration of international exchange programs for both faculty and cadets  Programs include Military Exchange Programs  Study Abroad  Virginia Program at Oxford and International Internships  Location  Old Hospital Phone   540  464 7421 Web Site   http www vmi edu Content aspx id 4294969511 Cadet Accounting   Cadet Accounting is responsible for maintaining records of cadets  financial obligations and payments  billing  and providing check cashing services  Location  310 Smith Hall Phone   540  464 7217 Web Site http www vmi edu Administration Finance Administration Support Comptrollers Office Accounts Payable Office Accounts Payable Office  Commandant s Office   The Commandant of Cadets  under the direction of the Superintendent  is responsible for the military training  appearance  and conduct of the Corps of Cadets  including discipline  The Commandant and his staff provide oversight to the barracks environment to include supervising the cadet regiment and class government organizations  The Commandant coordinates all phases of cadet life and scheduling to ensure cadets are present and fit for academic  military  and athletic duties  Location  Jackson Arch   Barracks Phone   540  464 7313 Web Site   http www vmi edu Content aspx id 4441 Writing Center   The purpose of the Writing Center is to provide non evaluative guidance to cadets who desire to improve their writing  The assistance is meant to complement academic activities and to extend the writing instruction that cadets receive in the classroom  Cadets may sign up or walk in for one on one tutoring outside of 323 Scott Shipp Hall  Location  323 Scott Shipp Hall and Satellite Offices Phone   540  464 7045 Web Site http www vmi edu Content aspx id 30509 NCAA Advising   NCAA advising provides mentoring  counseling  advising  academic assistance to athletes  and support for departmental academic advisors to enable VMI cadet athletes to maintain a balanced program in which they can excel athletically and academically  Location  205 Carroll Hall Phone   540  464 7722 Web Site   http www vmi edu content aspx tid 22373 id 3415 Advanced Placement and Transfer Credit Prior to Admission   VMI recognizes the College Board s Advanced Placement tests  and the International Baccalaureate Diploma and courses  For detail information concerning the requirements to academic credit  please see guidelines in the VMI Catalogue  Dual enrollment  attendance at other schools and VMI summer sessions  transfer credit is subject to approval of the appropriate curricular head  A minimum grade of C must be achieve to receive transfer credit  Location  Admissions Office Phone   540  464 7211 Web Site  http admissions vmi edu apply prepare requirements toggle id 2    AP IB credit http admissions vmi edu apply transfers  Transfer Students http admissions vmi edu apply prepare requirements toggle id 2  Dual Enrollment Undergraduate Research   VMI s Undergraduate Research Initiative was established to expand meaningful academic experiences for cadets via one on one interactions with faculty mentors to discuss  develop and complete research in a variety of venues  Location  302 Science Building Phone   540  464 7031 Web Site   http www vmi edu Content aspx id 126 Dean s Office   VMI s acting dean is Colonel Robert McDonald Location  210 Smith Hall Phone   540  464 7212 Web Site http www vmi edu Content aspx id 192 VMI Infirmary   VMI provides medical services on 24 hours  7 days a week while the Corps is in residence during the fall and spring semesters  Summer hours are 8 00 a m  to 4 00 p m  Monday through Friday during the summer  Location  VMI Infirmary Phone   540  464 7218 Web Site   http www vmi edu Administration Finance Administration Support VMI Infirmary Infirmary Home  VMI Catalogue can be obtained on the web at http www vmi edu Content aspx id 148   To obtain transfer credit after admission  please see requirements for graduation  Information was on material found in the VMI Catalogue  on the VMI Web Site  and the VMI Directory  Col  Francis Bush Home Courses Links For My Advisees VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 